com/api/questions/24884/relationships/activeRevision"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"17711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"packs":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/packs","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/packs"}},"revisions":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/revisions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/revisions"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"24884"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"101157"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"675"},{"type":"tags","id":"1487"},{"type":"tags","id":"1987"},{"type":"tags","id":"1993"},{"type":"tags","id":"2030"},{"type":"tags","id":"4097"},{"type":"tags","id":"4970"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9663"},{"type":"tags","id":"11432"},{"type":"tags","id":"11931"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"},{"type":"tags","id":"13209"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"52672"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/17711/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"119342","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic requesting information about preventing sexually transmitted infections. He has sex with men and reports having multiple partners with occasional condomless sex. He has a history of treated syphilis and recurrent chlamydia infections over the past two years. He has no other significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He is currently on pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) for HIV prevention.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There are no genital lesions or discharge present. He asks about taking antibiotics after sexual encounters to prevent STIs.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about doxycycline post-exposure prophylaxis (Doxy-PEP) is most accurate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It should be taken daily regardless of sexual activity","It is contraindicated in patients taking PrEP","It replaces the need for regular STI screening","It must be taken within 72 hours of condomless sex","It is effective against preventing chlamydia and gonorrhoea"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDoxycycline post-exposure prophylaxis (Doxy-PEP) is an emerging strategy for preventing bacterial sexually transmitted infections in high-risk populations, particularly men who have sex with men. Doxy-PEP has been shown to significantly reduce rates of syphilis and chlamydia infections.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt must be taken within 72 hours of condomless sex\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. The recommended protocol is to take doxycycline 200mg (two 100mg tablets) as soon as possible within 72 hours after condomless sex. The maximum dose is 200mg per day, regardless of the number of sexual encounters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt should be taken daily regardless of sexual activity\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Doxy-PEP is an on-demand strategy, not a daily prophylaxis. It should only be taken after potential exposure through condomless sex.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is effective against all chlamydia and gonorrhoea\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While doxy-PEP is highly effective against syphilis (approximately 87% reduction) and chlamydia (approximately 88% reduction), its effectiveness against gonorrhoea is limited in Australia due to high rates of doxycycline resistance in \u003Cem\u003ENeisseria gonorrhoeae\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt replaces the need for regular STI screening\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Regular STI screening remains essential for people using doxy-PEP. The Australian guidelines recommend screening every three months for those at ongoing risk, as doxy-PEP does not prevent all infections and does not protect against viral STIs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is contraindicated in patients taking PrEP\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. There is no contraindication to using doxy-PEP alongside HIV PrEP. In fact, many candidates for doxy-PEP are already on PrEP, as both strategies target populations at high risk for STIs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImportant considerations for doxy-PEP include potential side effects such as gastrointestinal upset and photosensitivity, the risk of developing antimicrobial resistance, and the need for ongoing monitoring. It should be prescribed as part of a comprehensive sexual health strategy that includes regular screening, vaccination where appropriate, and counselling about risk reduction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Doxycycline post-exposure prophylaxis (doxy-PEP) involves taking 200mg within 72 hours of condomless sex to prevent bacterial STIs.","Doxy-PEP is highly effective in preventing syphilis and chlamydia but has limited efficacy against gonorrhoea in Australia due to high resistance rates."],"references":["Australasian Society for HIV, Viral Hepatitis and Sexual Health Medicine (ASHM). Doxy-PEP Information Sheet. 2025. Available at: https://ashm.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/HEM_ASHM-Doxy-PEP-Infomation-Sheet.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"101157"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"24884"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/119342/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"